DOC.brief_summary: This study was designed to analyze whether initiation of the NICHD Neonatal Research Network SUPPORT trial was followed by a change in frequency of endotracheal intubation the delivery room in non-participants and whether these changes were associated with changes in management and outcomes. The investigators hypothesized that the investigators would observe following the initiation of the SUPPORT trial a 33% reduction in the rate of intubation in the delivery room among non-participants preterm infants at Parkland Memorial Hospital.
DOC.brief_title: Delivery Room Practice Change Following the Initiation of the NICHD SUPPORT Trial
DOC.criteria: All babies born at Parkland Memorial Hospital with gestational age at least 24 weeks and less than 35 weeks between 01/2003 and 06/2010 Infants receiving comfort care Those with major congenital anomalies Those enrolled in the SUPPORT trial
